# Taste Skill (installed)

Source: https://github.com/leonxlnx/taste-skill

Project skill paths:

- `.agents/skills/design-taste-frontend/` — default **v2** taste skill (`design-taste-frontend`)
- `.agents/skills/redesign-existing-projects/` — audit-then-fix existing UI (`redesign-existing-projects`)

Also present: Hallmark at `.agents/skills/hallmark/` (see `hallmark.mdc`).

## When to load

| Ask | Load |
| --- | --- |
| Landing page, marketing surface, portfolio-style promo, “taste skill”, anti-slop frontend | `design-taste-frontend/SKILL.md` |
| Redesign / upgrade an **existing** screen without a greenfield rebuild | `redesign-existing-projects/SKILL.md` (then taste dials if needed) |
| Ops console, dense tables, multi-step product workflows, Hermès corporate theme | Prefer **Hallmark** + Bisync Hermès defaults in `hallmark.mdc` |

Taste Skill itself notes it is for landings / portfolios / redesigns — **not** dashboards, data tables, or multi-step product UI. For those, do not force Taste Skill aesthetics over Hallmark + existing Bisync chrome.

## Bisync constraints (always)

1. Read the skill file first; follow its brief-inference / dial / pre-flight steps.
2. Prefer in-place edits; do not bulldoze routes or ownership (`structure-ownership.mdc`).
3. Keep live Hermès-on-white product chrome unless the user asks for a different marketing theme:
   - Ground `#FFFFFF` · Accent `#F37021` · Ink `#2A2118`
4. Respect currency / country formatters and component-identity rules when touching money or ingredients UI.

## Dial defaults for Bisync marketing (when using taste-skill)

Unless the brief says otherwise:

- Landing / promo: variance mid-high, motion moderate, density low–mid
- Trust / B2B procurement: lower variance + motion; keep Hermès orange as the single accent
- Never default to purple AI gradients, Inter-only stacks, or ivory/cream grounds that fight the live platform theme

